Leaf Leap Game There is allowed up to 4 players maximum. Four pebble pieces that are colored Yellow, Pink, Blue, and Purple There is a board layed out across the ground with a rectangular border made of four long straight sticks. The board is 6 feet in length and 3 feet in width. Inside the rectangle is a bunch of trails of flat rocks, intertwining and connecting in different ways. Randomly placed are orange, green, and red colored rocks.
  • red rocks: Mean move back a space
  • Green rocks: Mean earn a leaf
  • Orange rocks: mean a different action: Squirrel or Fence
Squirrel can mean: Move back 2-3 spaces Lose 1 leaf Swap leaves Gain 1 leaf Fence means: Skip your turn Green rock means you will be given a wheel to spin for either a green, red, or orange leaf. Each one with their value. Green: +1 Red: +2 Orange: +3 There is one Acorn with three sides that have a one, two, or a three claw mark(s). Once rolled whichever side it lands on it will determine how many spaces your pebble will move. There are 30, 40, or 50, spaces depending on how long of a game is wanted. The person to get to the last pebble wins the game and gets the title of the day BUT the person with the most leaves gets to tell the other three what to do for the next few hours. Those are the rewards. The way of determining what an acorns answer will be, what stone you'll land on, or what you‚Äôll get will be by a wheel or dice on an online website.
12:36 PM
Gameplay; Once collected your pebble of choice, each character roles three acorns. The one with the highest number will go first, the second highest will go next, the third most goes and the lowest will be the last. (This will be determined by a dice online) Once figured who goes in which order they place their pebbles at the beginning starting rock. The first person rolls 1 die and gets an answer. (Rolled 1 die online) the amount from 1-3 they will move that many. If they get 1 count on the die, they will move their pebble one rock forward. If it's 3 then they will move three! Then there's a spin of a wheel to determine what they land on. A regular move rock or a red, green, or orange rock? Once everyone starts there's way and someone lands on a colorful rock this will be how it goes; Green rock; wheel will have three options - green, red, or an orange leaf.
  • Green Leaf - +1 leaf
  • Red Leaf - +2 leaves
  • Orange Leaf - +3 leave
Adds to their collection! Red Rock: they move back however many spaces the wheel chooses. 1-6 spaces max. Orange Rock: the wheel chooses either squirrel or fence. Squirrel gives the reward or obsticle And Fence skips your turn ‚ñ∫ to keep track out of roleplay where they are here is a chart to fill out in the beginning of the roleplay post.
